Due to limited seating capacity at Carlisle‚Äôs stadium, there will only be approximately 130 tickets available for this week‚Äôs game.

Tickets will be dispersed in the following manner:

‚Ä¢ All senior football, cheer, and band participants will receive 2 tickets.

‚Ä¢ All other varsity football participants will receive 2 tickets.

‚Ä¢ Remaining band and cheer participants will be notified on Tuesday if their names were drawn to receive tickets. Those selected will have until Wednesday afternoon to purchase their tickets.

‚Ä¢ Any tickets still available on Thursday will first be offered to participants whose names were not initially drawn.

*All tickets are $5.00.

There will no live-streaming this week due to Carlisle‚Äôs press box limitations. Carlisle ISD is still in the process of launching their live-streaming. Alto fans will have the opportunity to purchase pay-per-view through Carlisle ISD if they go live.

Thank you for your continued support of our Alto Yellowjackets!

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT:

Out of an abundance of caution for our kids, teachers, and drivers ..... we will be cancelling school on Thursday, August 27 due to Hurricane Laura.

We do not want to jeopardize buses being on the roads, kids in portable buildings, or staff members traveling to and from work.

This will include canceling the JV football game in Troup, as well as any after school practices or activities.

Friday will be a wait-and-see based on conditions and power.

Player/participant weekly football tickets:

As a surprise to our senior families ... all senior participants will receive the option to purchase an additional 10 family hillside tickets for all home games. Families that purchase these will need to bring lawn chairs or blankets for seating.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Directions in comments.

ATTENTION PARENTS of 6th GRADERS and SENIORS:

All 6th grade students are required to have vaccinations prior to starting 7th grade. Seniors are required to have their meningococcal vaccine before college entry. If you signed up for a clinic appointment at AISD, it was cancelled due to Covid19. I will be available at the Elementary campus May 14 and 15 from 9:00-11:00am and 12:00-2:00pm, to provide your refunded money if you paid in advance.
I must have proof of vaccinations before your child can be given a 7th grade schedule. You can fax records to 936-858-4382. Please email me at kholmes@alto.esc7.net with any questions or concerns.
Thank you, Mrs. Kimmie

Dear Class of 2020,
Our intention is to hold your graduation ceremony on Cam‚ÄôRon Matthews Field, as long as we are permitted to do so by the State. We are closely following all updates from the Governor‚Äôs Office and Education Commissioner. At this time, school functions are not allowed until the end of May. Yesterday, the Commissioner stated that he hopes to have further graduation guidance for schools next week. In the event that a traditional ceremony on the field is not possible, we do have an alternate plan in place. Please be patient and know that we are trying to adapt to this situation and celebrate our Class of 2020. Also, understand that if a group ceremony is allowed to happen, there will most likely still be restrictions in place. We will communicate updates to all of you as soon as we have a definite answer! üñ§üíõüéìüêù

ALTO ISD has been actively monitoring the COVID-19 situation.

This afternoon, Governor Abbott released an executive order for the state. In compliance with this order, Alto ISD will remain closed until at least May 4th.

We realize that this is a difficult time for many. As a school district, our priority will always be the safety and security of our students, staff, and community as a whole. This is an unprecedented situation for all school districts throughout the state, and these decisions are not taken lightly.

We will continue to announce updates and information through our district website, our district Facebook page, and our automated phone system.

Stay at home. Stay safe.

Change in Grab & Go Meals

In an attempt to help reduce daily interactions, we are moving our meal pick-up to once a week versus a daily pick-up. The meal bags will include five breakfast items and five lunches.

Weekly pick-ups will be on Mondays from 11:00am-1:00pm. To reserve meals for your household, please call 936-858-7126 between 5:00pm-7:00pm Sunday evening or Monday morning from 8:00-9:00. Remember all children under 18 qualify for these meals.

Meals can be picked up daily in the Elementary School pick-up line between 11:30-1:00 each day.
We encourage all of our families to use this outreach to aid in this stressful time.

post_text:
Nothing honors a school more than having a former student return to encourage your current students.

Today, AHS was blessed by the encouraging words of Jacolby Whitaker, 2014 AHS graduate. While at AHS Jacolby was a member of National Honor Society and Student Council. His accomplishments, in sports, include being a 2X All State football player and a member of the 2014 Track and Field State Champion team.

Jacolby continued his education at SFA as a member of the football team from 2014-2017.
He graduated in December 2017 with a Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology. He carried the honor of a Magna Cum Laude graduate.
Currently, this AHS graduate, is enrolled in the Graduate Athletic Training Program with an expected graduation date of May 2020. Jacolby will then hold a Masters in Sports Medicine.

From Alto Booster Club:

FOOTBALL BANQUET RSVPs due!
SIGN UP for the upcoming Alto Football Banquet by this Friday, January 10th.

The Alto Football Banquet is Monday, January 20th at 6:00 p.m. at The Legacy in Jacksonville. We will recognize and celebrate all football players, cheerleaders, trainers, and audio visual crew for the 2019 season. This includes Varsity and JV!

In the comments below, you will find a RSVP form. Simply fill out the form and return with your payment to the Alto High School office, Coach Meeks, OR you can run it by Duplichain Contractors. There will be a fajita buffet dinner, awards recognizing outstanding achievement, including district and all-state accolades, and a highlight video of our great season! Cost is $15 a person, but the students who are being recognized are free! List on the RSVP form your player and the guests coming in honor of that player. No player? Just fill in your name and return it with your payment. Sunday dress.
